Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Ultimately, what ZER marketing doesn't realize, is that zero fee transactions are a nice-to-have when blocks are empty. They are also an attack vector. And when blocks are full, they don't work. Fees make blockchains go, it's incentive for a miner to include your transaction in a block

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Miners decide which transaction fees to accept, not the coin devs, and not the people sending the transactions. Only the miners

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> They have full control of that aspect of the network

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Right now, in the ZEC network, if you use fee=0, you will be censored by 90% of mining pools

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> Your transaction might work, but most likely it will expire. Zcash invented the whole expiring bullshit to basically solve this problem, it seems
